cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.CR 

The paper deals with a distributed setting where samples are divided between multiple users, and the authors provide a complete understanding of the interplay between the amount of shared randomness available, the stringency of information constraints, and the sample complexity of the testing problem. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
